com.ai

Class NanoParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ai.AbstractNanoParser<ASTCell,NanoTokens>
      • com.ai.NanoParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parser<ASTCell,NanoTokens>

    public class NanoParser
extends AbstractNanoParser<ASTCell,NanoTokens>

    Concrete Parser object used to parse a NanoC file into an AbstractSyntax tree.

    Creates an Abstract Syntax tree by means of Recursive Descent Parsing with each node on tree represented as an ASTCell object

    Comprised of individual parse statements that each represent a specific non-terminal or terminal inside the NanoC grammer

    There is also a helper method that creates a given ASTCell from a specific operator. infixOpSel(NanoTokens, ASTCell, ASTCell)

    Author:
    Martin Tice

      • parse

        public void parse()
        First/only method needed by client after initialization. Parses a file into an ASTCell. begins by creating a random NumberASTCell(CAN CHANGE IN FUTURE).

        gets the next token in a file, decides what non-terminal it represents the start of, and delegates further parsing to a specific parse method

        Continues This process until the end of file is reached.
